post_text: Thank you ES Tech!!!
shared_text:
Eastern Slope Rural Telephone Assoc., Inc.
February 26 at 5:00 PM ¬∑

As part of our technology outreach, Eastern Slope (ESTech) recently presented the Woodlin and Flagler Schools with a technology donation. The schools were asked to compile a ‚Äúwish list‚Äù. The Woodlin School indicated that the $1,500 would be used for the purchase of Adobe Creative Cloud software for the district, benefiting the students in art and CTE courses. The Flagler School will use the $1500 to purchase Chromebooks for the K-2 classrooms. As your local communications cooperative, Eastern Slope understands the importance of collaboration between entities to attain a mutual goal. We are honored to be able to reinforce the vital role that technology plays in our rural communities and schools through this donation. Pat Ensign White, Arriba-Flagler School District, Flagler Senior High School, Woodlin School District R-104

post_text: Congratulations to the Woodlin FFA members who participated in NJC CDE Contest. In Floriculture, Andrea Esobedo received a gold award and was District 9 high individual. Dannica Kalcevic received a Silver and Chris Wood received a Bronze. The Floriculture team received a Silver award which also included Ember Quick, Gihven Tucker, and Jerica Salser. Andrea, Dannica, Ember, and Chris qualified for State. Henry Goff received a Bronze award and was the high individual in the District and qualified for State in Vet Tech Science. Kenize Phelps also participated in Livestock judging contest.
